<div id="review_1335845192" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1335845192" />
    <a title="Chuck" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5091581-chuck"><img alt="Chuck" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1330829413p2/5091581.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1335845192?book_show_action=true">Jul 15, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Chuck" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Chuck" href="/user/show/5091581-chuck">Chuck</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781586487072" href="/book/show/6457760-my-guantanamo-diary">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=namerica">namerica</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=owned">owned</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=arab-themes">arab-themes</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=review">review</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=military-war">military-war</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=biography">biography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5091581-chuck?shelf=oceana-other">oceana-other</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1335845192" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18344102237922291285">This book was written by a young woman that was raised in the United States, but of Afghan heritage. She speaks Pashto fluently and became in the defense of detainees at Guantanamo first as a translator and then as a law student from the University of Michigan. Her principal purpose for this book was to reflect her opinion that the military base at Guantanamo should never have been used for these purposes and that the detainees all had a right to have their stories told in court or by some other</span>
  <span id="freeText18344102237922291285" style="display:none">This book was written by a young woman that was raised in the United States, but of Afghan heritage. She speaks Pashto fluently and became in the defense of detainees at Guantanamo first as a translator and then as a law student from the University of Michigan. Her principal purpose for this book was to reflect her opinion that the military base at Guantanamo should never have been used for these purposes and that the detainees all had a right to have their stories told in court or by some other responsible tribunal. After reading this excellent book, I completely agree. It is clear that many that were incarcerated at Gitmo were innocent. My problem with the book is that every detainee that she discusses at length is innocent and abused by the people of our military and their superiors. I do not believe that this is true. It would bw aimilar to someone thinking that each and every prisoner were guilty if the book had been written by a marine. My opinion is that this book was well intended but written by a young arab woman with an agenda to prove. The overwhelming motive that the book has left me with, at best, is naivette. </span>
  <a data-text-id="18344102237922291285" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


