<div id="review_1708542048" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1708542048" />
    <a title="Carla" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7965254-carla"><img alt="Carla" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1470265243p2/7965254.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1708542048?book_show_action=true">Jul 25, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carla" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carla" href="/user/show/7965254-carla">Carla</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1708542048" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16801547456979342168">A very well written book about the detainees at Guantanamo. The writer, a daughter of Afghan immigrants writes this story after having been at first a translator for the pro bono lawyers seeking to assist the detainees. She brings a wonderful look at the men she spoke to, who, for some, were at the wrong place at the wrong time. She herself states that there might be people there, that she did not see, did not talk to, that are dangerous. However she offers an insightful, humane look at the deta</span>
  <span id="freeText16801547456979342168" style="display:none">A very well written book about the detainees at Guantanamo. The writer, a daughter of Afghan immigrants writes this story after having been at first a translator for the pro bono lawyers seeking to assist the detainees. She brings a wonderful look at the men she spoke to, who, for some, were at the wrong place at the wrong time. She herself states that there might be people there, that she did not see, did not talk to, that are dangerous. However she offers an insightful, humane look at the detainees she did have access to, and tells us about them, their perspectives, their hopes for a future, not confined. <br />Mahvish writes a book, everyone should be reading. Anyone who at any time in their lives is concerned about human rights. It didn't take long for me to finish this. I'm glad I read this, but am ashamed that it still continues. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16801547456979342168" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


